Women in Africa Initiative President, Hafsat Abiola-Costello, will be the keynote speaker at the International Women’s Day virtual conference with the theme: Choose to challenge. It will be hosted by CWG Plc, one of Africa’s leading tech solutions provider. CWQ Senior Brand Strategist, Ms Seun Koshoedo, said the session will hold on Friday and that participants can register via https://bit.ly/3r5DV4v. Genevieve magazine founder Betty Irabor will be among the speakers. The event will focus on taking female leadership to a new level and breaking new frontiers in technology, entertainment, finance. 